    "As indicated in Table 6, 14% of the predictions for the gold-standard test set, although lacking a strict match, exhibit a 100 Similarly, for Cohort-Short and Cohort-Long, respectively, 7% and 15% of the predicted answers have a 100% overlap with the gold-standard answers while not having a strict match.",
